
[1]rumination

   RUMINA'TION, n. [L. ruminatio.]

   1. The act of chewing the cud.

   2. The power or property of chewing the cud.

   Rumination is given to animals, to enable them at once to lay up a
   great store of food, and afterwards to chew it.

   3. A musing or continued thinking on a subject; deliberate meditation
   or reflection.

   Retiring full of rumination sad.
